<span id="freeTextContainer13939420934274626634">I didn&apos;t even have to think about the 5 stars given this book. Powerful writing, powerful characters, powerful themes; this is what great literature is meant to be. I consider the controversy surrounding this book to be an indication of it&apos;s excellence. I won&apos;t bother to give a synopsis of the plot, but I will say it paints a painful and depressing view of the institution of slavery and it&apos;s effect on white and black people, creating less than human roles for both races. I&apos;m glad I finally got a</span>
  <span id="freeText13939420934274626634" style="display:none">I didn't even have to think about the 5 stars given this book. Powerful writing, powerful characters, powerful themes; this is what great literature is meant to be. I consider the controversy surrounding this book to be an indication of it's excellence. I won't bother to give a synopsis of the plot, but I will say it paints a painful and depressing view of the institution of slavery and it's effect on white and black people, creating less than human roles for both races. I'm glad I finally got around to reading this novel, thanks to my GR group, "On the Southern Literary Trail".</span>
